<subSubSection id="C3786552C64EFFBEBA8FFBEAB45BFB17" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDD36D9C64EFFBEBA8FFBEAB062FBB7" blockId="17.[227,348,1082,1108]" box="[227,348,1082,1108]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<heading id="D09581B5C64EFFBEBA8FFBEAB062FBB7" bold="true" box="[227,348,1082,1108]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC64EFFBEBA8FFBEAB062FBB7" bold="true" box="[227,348,1082,1108]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDD36D9C64EFFBEBA8FFBBAB45BFB17" blockId="17.[226,1437,1130,1268]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC64EFFBEBA8FFBBAB045FB67" authorityName="Chamberlin" authorityYear="1919" box="[227,379,1130,1156]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="17" pageNumber="59" phylum="Annelida" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pelogeniinae">Pelogeniinae</taxonomicName>
with prostomium oval, longer than wide. Upper lip with or without facial tubercle. Median antennal ceratophore bulbous, base without ctenidia. Segment II without middorsal lobe; neuropodia without appendages; neurochaetal blades bifid, falcate. Segment III without dorsal cirri; neuropodia without appendages; neurochaetal blades bifid. First pair of elytra enlarged, rarely deeply notched.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
