<subSubSection id="C3786552C64DFFBDBA8FFD0BB31DFB7C" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDD36D9C64DFFBDBA8FFD0BB06BFD16" blockId="18.[227,341,731,757]" box="[227,341,731,757]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<heading id="D09581B5C64DFFBDBA8FFD0BB06BFD16" bold="true" box="[227,341,731,757]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC64DFFBDBA8FFD0BB06BFD16" bold="true" box="[227,341,731,757]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDD36D9C64DFFBDBA8FFCDCB31DFB7C" blockId="18.[225,1438,780,1183]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC64DFFBDBA8FFCDCB329FCC5" box="[227,535,780,806]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Psammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="sombreriana">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC64DFFBDBA8FFCDCB329FCC5" box="[227,535,780,806]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Psammolyce sombreriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was the name introduced by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C64DFFBDB9EAFCDCB5AEFCC5" author="McIntosh W. C." box="[902,1168,780,807]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 554" refId="ref30050" refString="McIntosh W. C. 1885. On the Annelida Polychaeta collected by H. S. M. Challenger during the years 1873 - 1876. Challenger reports 12 (34): 1 - 554." type="journal article" year="1885">
McIntosh (1885: 149
<emphasis id="B916EACBC64DFFBDBEEAFCDCB5AEFCC5" box="[1158,1168,780,806]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC64DFFBDBEA4FCDDB449FCC5" baseAuthorityName="McIntosh" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[1224,1399,780,806]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Neopsammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC64DFFBDBEA4FCDDB449FCC5" box="[1224,1399,780,806]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">P. occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC64DFFBDBA8FFCE2B0ABFCA8" baseAuthorityName="McIntosh" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[227,405,817,843]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Neopsammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC64DFFBDBA8FFCE2B0ABFCA8" box="[227,405,817,843]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">N. occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), which possibly resulted from a confusion. In the discussion section of 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC64DFFBDBF6EFCE2B445FCAF" authorityName="McIntosh" authorityYear="1885" box="[1282,1403,818,844]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Psammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fijiensis">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC64DFFBDBF6EFCE2B445FCAF" box="[1282,1403,818,844]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">P. fijiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC64DFFBDBA89FC87B3EFFC91" authority="(McIntosh, 1885)" baseAuthorityName="McIntosh" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[229,721,855,882]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Pottsipelogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fijiensis">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC64DFFBDBA89FC87B0C5FC92" box="[229,507,855,881]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Pottsipelogenia fijiensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C64DFFBDB864FC87B3F6FC91" author="McIntosh W. C." box="[520,712,855,882]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 554" refId="ref30050" refString="McIntosh W. C. 1885. On the Annelida Polychaeta collected by H. S. M. Challenger during the years 1873 - 1876. Challenger reports 12 (34): 1 - 554." type="journal article" year="1885">McIntosh, 1885</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
], McIntosh noted the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC64DFFBDBE63FC88B581FC92" box="[1039,1215,855,881]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Psammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="sombreriana">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC64DFFBDBE63FC88B581FC92" box="[1039,1215,855,881]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">P. sombreriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, possibly referring to 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC64DFFBDBB6DFCAEB092FC74" baseAuthorityName="McIntosh" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[257,428,893,919]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Neopsammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC64DFFBDBB6DFCAEB092FC74" box="[257,428,893,919]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">P. occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was the first name that he came up for the species; however, since he kept this honest mistake in the final version of his contribution, the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC64DFFBDB9B3FC73B5ACFC5E" box="[991,1170,931,957]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Psammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="sombreriana">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC64DFFBDB9B3FC73B5ACFC5E" box="[991,1170,931,957]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">P. sombreriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a nomen nudum. In any case, the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC64DFFBDBBAEFC19B34DFC01" box="[450,627,968,994]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Psammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="sombreriana">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC64DFFBDBBAEFC19B34DFC01" box="[450,627,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">P. sombreriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would reflect the fact that his specimens came from Sombrero Island, Antilles. On the other hand, 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC64DFFBDB854FC3EB519FBEB" authority="(Hartman, 1939)" baseAuthorityName="Hartman" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[568,1063,1006,1032]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Neopsammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC64DFFBDB854FC3EB265FBEB" box="[568,859,1006,1032]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Neopsammolyce spinosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C64DFFBDB907FC3EB521FBEB" author="Hartman O." box="[875,1055,1006,1032]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 156" refId="ref29485" refString="Hartman O. 1939. Polychaetous annelids, 1: Aphroditidae to Pisionidae. Allan Hancock Pacific Expeditions 7 (1): 1 - 156." type="journal article" year="1939">Hartman, 1939</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
was described from the Pacific coast of 
<collectingCountry id="F3757649C64DFFBDBB21FBC4B0EAFBCD" box="[333,468,1044,1070]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C64DFFBDB8E4FBC4B26DFBCD" author="Pettibone M. H." box="[648,851,1044,1070]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 89" refId="ref30430" refString="Pettibone M. H. 1997. Revision of the sigalionid species (Polychaeta) referred to Psammolyce Kinberg, 1856, Pelogenia Schmarda, 1861, and belonging to the subfamily Pelogeniinae Chamberlin, 1919. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 581: 1 - 89. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.581" type="journal article" year="1997">Pettibone (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, the record of this species from Galeta, 
<collectingCountry id="F3757649C64DFFBDBF53FBC4B4A2FBCD" box="[1343,1436,1044,1070]" name="Panama" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Panama</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C64DFFBDBA87FBE9B0F0FBB7" author="Fauchald K." box="[235,462,1081,1108]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 81" refId="ref29238" refString="Fauchald K. 1977. Polychaetes from intertidal areas in Panama, with a review of previous shallow-water records. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 221: 1 - 81. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.221" type="journal article" year="1977">Fauchald 1977: 62</bibRefCitation>
) corresponded to 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC64DFFBDB8C5FBE9B54DFBB7" authority="(Hartman, 1939)" baseAuthorityName="Hartman" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[681,1139,1081,1108]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Pelogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="anoculata">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC64DFFBDB8C5FBE9B2A1FBB0" box="[681,927,1081,1107]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Pelogenia anoculata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C64DFFBDB9DEFBEAB554FBB7" author="Hartman O." box="[946,1130,1082,1108]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 156" refId="ref29485" refString="Hartman O. 1939. Polychaetous annelids, 1: Aphroditidae to Pisionidae. Allan Hancock Pacific Expeditions 7 (1): 1 - 156." type="journal article" year="1939">Hartman, 1939</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, also described from the Pacific coast of 
<collectingCountry id="F3757649C64DFFBDBBC4FB8FB30EFB9A" box="[424,560,1119,1145]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
. However, the form recorded by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C64DFFBDB9A4FB8FB5B3FB9A" author="Fauchald K." box="[968,1165,1119,1145]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 81" refId="ref29238" refString="Fauchald K. 1977. Polychaetes from intertidal areas in Panama, with a review of previous shallow-water records. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 221: 1 - 81. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.221" type="journal article" year="1977">Fauchald (1977)</bibRefCitation>
is described below as 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC64DFFBDBA8FFB55B0FFFB7C" authority="Cruz-Gómez, 2022" authorityName="Cruz-Gómez" authorityYear="2022" box="[227,449,1157,1183]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Pelogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="capitata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC64DFFBDBA8FFB55B0FFFB7C" box="[227,449,1157,1183]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Pelogenia capitata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22557B0C64DFFBDBBA4FB55B31DFB7C" box="[456,547,1157,1183]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
